AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Time to incrementally refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every incremental refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The incremental refresh is much lighter, less expensive and therefore can be completed quicker than a total refresh, but will not detect deletions of master data records.
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.

This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Search Key
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Obpos_Format_Group
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
Character used when displaying numeric values in Web POS to separate thousands groups (typically "," or ".").
In case this value is not set, it will be defaulted to the one defined in Format.xml.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Usebarcodescanner
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Check this property when an external barcode scanner will be used with this terminal type
AD_COLUMN.HELP:
If this property is checked, the Web POS will take into account that an external input (keyboard or barcode scanner) is going to be used in this POS terminal type. Checking this option and then not connecting an external inout will cause the virtual keyboard to be shown continuously in some devices (specifically, in iOS devices (iPads, iPhones)).
If this option is not checked, then the barcode scanners will not be detected in the application even if they are correctly connected to the system.
